arStrings.szText: Three workers fled in the night, and by the sound of morale, more are behind them. They say the mine is cursed. Maybe it is, but we’ve a job to finish.
Matter of fact. Not very sympathetic to people's fears, but not entirely heartless. Just wants to get the job done.

Old superstitions say Khazra bones ward against curses. I’ve never put much stock in old wives’ tales, but if it keeps folk from fleeing, I’ll wear them myself, eh? (laughs) I have no men to go hunting, but I have coin. It's yours if you collect some bones.
